{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-jsx","path":"/posts/2019-01-19---buidling-a-web-site-with-gatsby/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Blog & Profile by Aleksandar Ristevski","subtitle":"Any sufficiently advanced technology is indistinguishable from magic.","copyright":"All rights reserved <br> Copyright © 2018 - 2021","author":{"name":"Aleksandar Ristevski","twitter":"@nicewaytodoit"},"disqusShortname":"","siteUrl":"https://nicewaytodoit.github.io/aleksandar.ristevski.me"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"87c45fd3-cef6-5029-912f-9776f9db02bf","html":"<p>Gatsby should be a modern framework for the fast websites. Project was born in May 2015 as a simple way to build a website with React.</p>\n<p>But become increasingly popular around mid 2017. </p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 840px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/042dd29755cb80419c34f3498118bd0b/bba1f/1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 25.83333333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"GatsbyJS Popularity Growth\"\n        title=\"GatsbyJS Popularity Growth\"\n        src=\"/static/042dd29755cb80419c34f3498118bd0b/bba1f/1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/042dd29755cb80419c34f3498118bd0b/09b79/1.jpg 240w,\n/static/042dd29755cb80419c34f3498118bd0b/7cc5e/1.jpg 480w,\n/static/042dd29755cb80419c34f3498118bd0b/bba1f/1.jpg 840w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>This is just a first test page, and it will not give you much about Gatsby. So, maybe I need a todo list of what I want to achieve?</p>\n<p>Here it is: </p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Installation - Setup/Templates/Plugins…</p>\n<p>Everything starts with:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">$ <span class=\"token function\">npm</span> init gatsby</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>Assembling bits - trying to find the relation between React components, static <code class=\"language-text\">.md</code> files and data.</li>\n<li>Exploring Gatsby and GraphQL </li>\n<li>Running - trying different scripts</li>\n<li>Deployment - Deployment to Github pages / Automated scripts </li>\n<li>\n<p>Issues </p>\n<ul>\n<li>protocols - </li>\n<li>long paths - it seems that some pre-processor is needed for links, they do not convert correctly </li>\n<li>prefix - ?\n…</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<p>For future references use the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.com/\">Gatsby Official Website</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.com/docs/quick-start/\">Gatsby Quick Start</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.com/starters/?\">Gatsby Templates</a></li>\n</ul>","fields":{"tagSlugs":["/tags/learning/","/tags/coding/","/tags/static-framework/","/tags/gatsby/"]},"timeToRead":1,"frontmatter":{"title":"Web site with Gatsby","tags":["Learning","Coding","Static Framework","Gatsby"],"date":"2019-01-19T23:26:33.333Z","description":"This is just test page, for future references it is best to visit Gatsby official website."}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/2019-01-19---buidling-a-web-site-with-gatsby/"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}